      "body": "**T13 genus-0 / Route-C retirement: `WeilDivisor.lean` is DUAL-PURPOSE \u2014 carve, do not delete.**\n\nThe genus split is *already* mostly retired: `Genus0BaseObjects.lean`, `AbelianVarietyRigidity.lean`, and `genusZeroWitness`/`positiveGenusWitness` are deleted; `Jacobian C` is uniform via `picardJacobianWitness`. The remaining T13 work is residue cleanup, with one dependency trap.\n\n**Trap \u2014 `AlgebraicJacobian/RiemannRoch/WeilDivisor.lean` serves two masters.**\n\n- Its `Scheme.PrimeDivisor` type and `Scheme.RationalMap.order : X.functionField \u2192 \u2124` valuation are the codim-1 substrate that `Albanese/CodimOneExtension.lean` (`ALB.codim1`, live north-star path) imports and uses \u2014 the `coheight = 1` convention (`CodimOneExtension.lean:177`) and the order-valuation appeal (`:1823`).\n- The `degree` / `degree_hom` / `principal_degree_zero` / `positivePart` / RR\u2192\u2119\u00b9 block (5 sorries, `-- Route C PAUSE`) exists only to prove the now-obsolete `genusZero_curve_iso_P1`. That block is the Route-C / genus-0 dead weight.\n\n**Consequence:** a wholesale delete of `WeilDivisor.lean` breaks the codim-1 extension build. The dependency-safe shape is a surgical carve of the RR/degree/\u2119\u00b9 portion plus the file header (which frames the whole file around `genusZero_curve_iso_P1`), retaining the `PrimeDivisor`/`order` substrate.\n\n**Also live, not genus-0:** `RigidityLemma.lean` and blueprint `AbelianVarietyRigidity.tex` are the sorry-free rigidity-lemma + Milne \u00a7I.1\u2013I.3 corollaries used by the uniform Albanese construction; only their \"feed the genus-0 base case (Route C)\" prose is stale \u2014 clean the prose, keep the math.",
